API docs by Redocly

Wsf Fares API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

Wsf Fares API - Washington State Department of Transportation APIs

cache-flush-date

Each CacheFlushDate item represents the timestamp when Washington State Ferries fare data was last updated in the system. This information helps applications determine when to refresh cached fare information.

Returns a single CacheFlushDate for the WSF fares system.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/cacheflushdate

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getCacheFlushDate } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getCacheFlushDate,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

"2025-11-04T19:37:56.870Z"

valid-date-range

Each ValidDateRange item represents the current validity period for Washington State Ferries fare data. This endpoint provides the start and end dates between which fare information is accurate and published for all ferry routes.

Returns a single ValidDateRange object for the current fares data validity period.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/validdaterange

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getFaresValidDateRange } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getFaresValidDateRange,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

{
  • "DateFrom": "2025-11-04T08:00:00.000Z",
  • "DateThru": "2026-03-21T07:00:00.000Z"
}

terminals

Each Terminal item represents a Washington State Ferries port facility with unique identification, location details, and operational status. These terminals serve as departure and arrival points for ferry routes throughout the Puget Sound and San Juan Islands.

Returns arriving terminals for the given departing terminal and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (TerminalMatesInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve arriving terminals, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter terminal mates by trip date availability.

TerminalID
required
number (TerminalMatesInputTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to filter arriving terminals by origin terminal.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminalMates/{TripDate}/{TerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getTerminalMates } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getTerminalMates,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06",
    "TerminalID": 1
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 4 total)

[
  • {
    • "TerminalID": 10,
    • "Description": "Friday Harbor"
    },
  • {
    • "_note": "... 3 more items"
    }
]

Returns a list of valid departing terminals for the specified trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FaresTerminalsInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve valid departing terminals, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025, '2026-03-21' for March 21, 2026. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter terminals by trip date availability.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminals/{TripDate}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getFaresTerminals } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getFaresTerminals,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 19 total)

[
  • {
    • "TerminalID": 1,
    • "Description": "Anacortes"
    },
  • {
    • "_note": "... 18 more items"
    }
]

terminal-combo

Each TerminalCombo item represents valid route pairings between Washington State Ferries terminals with associated fare collection methods and scheduling details. These combinations define which terminals are connected and how fares are collected for specific routes.

Returns fare collection descriptions for all terminal combinations available on the specified trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (TerminalComboVerboseInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for fare collection descriptions, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fare collection information by trip date.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminalComboVerbose/{TripDate}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getTerminalComboVerbose } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getTerminalComboVerbose,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 38 total)

[
  • {
    • "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    • "DepartingDescription": "Anacortes",
    • "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    • "ArrivingDescription": "Friday Harbor",
    • "CollectionDescription": "Passenger and vehicle/driver fares are collected at Anacortes, while no fares are collected at Friday Harbor."
    },
  • {
    • "_note": "... 37 more items"
    }
]

Returns fare collection descriptions for the specified terminal combination and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (TerminalComboInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for fare collection description, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fare collection information by trip date.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (TerminalComboInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for fare collection.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (TerminalComboInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals for departing terminal. Used to identify destination terminal for fare collection.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminalCombo/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getTerminalCombo } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getTerminalCombo,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

{
  • "DepartingDescription": "Anacortes",
  • "ArrivingDescription": "Friday Harbor",
  • "CollectionDescription": "Passenger and vehicle/driver fares are collected at Anacortes, while no fares are collected at Friday Harbor."
}

fare-line-items

Each FareLineItem item represents individual fare components for Washington State Ferries routes, including passenger categories, vehicle types, and pricing structures. These items form the building blocks for calculating total journey costs based on route, vehicle dimensions, and passenger demographics.

Returns multiple of FareLineItem for popular fare options.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FareLineItemsBasicInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for fare line items, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fares by trip date.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FareLineItemsBasicInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for fare calculation.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FareLineItemsBasicInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to identify destination terminal for fare calculation.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FareLineItemsBasicInputRoundTripParam)

Trip type indicator, as a boolean. E.g., true for round trip fares, false for one-way fares. Determines whether returned fares are for round trip or one-way journeys.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareLineItemsBasic/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getFareLineItemsBasic } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getFareLineItemsBasic,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "RoundTrip": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 12 total)

[
  • {
    • "FareLineItemID": 1,
    • "FareLineItem": "Adult (age 19 - 64)",
    • "Category": "Passenger",
    • "DirectionIndependent": false,
    • "Amount": 17.5
    },
  • {
    • "_note": "... 11 more items"
    }
]

Returns multiple of FareLineItem for specific terminal combination.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for fare line items, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fares by trip date.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for fare calculation.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to identify destination terminal for fare calculation.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputRoundTripParam)

Trip type indicator, as a boolean. E.g., true for round trip fares, false for one-way fares. Determines whether returned fares are for round trip or one-way journeys.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareLineItems/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminals } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminals,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-06",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 3,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 7,
    "RoundTrip": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

TripDate

Trip date for fare line items, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fares by trip date.

fare-totals

Each FareTotal item represents calculated fare costs for Washington State Ferries journeys based on selected fare line items and passenger quantities. These totals combine individual fare components to provide complete pricing for specific routes and travel scenarios.

Calculates total fares for the specified terminal combination, trip type, and selected fare line items with quantities.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for fare total calculation, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange. Used to filter fare calculations by trip date.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for fare calculation.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to identify destination terminal for fare calculation.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputRoundTripParam)

Trip type indicator, as a boolean. E.g., true for round trip fare totals, false for one-way fare totals. Determines whether totals include return journey fares.

FareLineItemID
required
string (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputFareLineItemIDParam)

Comma-separated list of fare line item IDs to include in total calculation, as a comma-delimited string. E.g., '1,2,3' for Adult, Senior, and Youth fares. Use GetFareLineItems to find valid fare line item IDs. Each ID corresponds to quantity at same index in Quantity array.

Quantity
required
string (FareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputQuantityParam)

Comma-separated list of quantities for corresponding fare line items, as a comma-delimited string. E.g., '2,1,0' for 2 adults, 1 senior, 0 youth. Values must be >= 0. Each quantity corresponds to fare line item ID at same index in FareLineItemID array.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareTotals/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}/{FareLineItemID}/{Quantity}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getFareTotalsByTripDateAndRoute } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getFareTotalsByTripDateAndRoute,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-05",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "RoundTrip": false,
    "FareLineItemID": "1,2",
    "Quantity": "3,1"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 3 total)

[
  • {
    • "TotalType": 1,
    • "Description": "Anacortes to Friday Harbor",
    • "BriefDescription": "Depart",
    • "Amount": 61.25
    },
  • {
    • "_note": "... 2 more items"
    }
]
